<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-21-0502 </DOCNO><TEXT>The planned construction of the reprocessing plant creates problems withregard to transfrontier environmental protection, due to the potentialhazards involved, and these problems institute obligations of the FederalRepublic of Germany under contractual law and under customary internationallaw. Particularly under customary international neighbour law the F.R.G.is obliged to prevent and abstain from transfrontier activities entailingenvironmental effects with considerable damaging potential in the neighbouringstates, which also includes the duty of providing for protection againstaccidents. It is, however, a clear fact that the states decided the peacefuluses of atomic energy to be admissible, and accept the risk of possiblecatastrophic damage. The interpretation of existing international lawshas to take this fact into account. (orig./HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>